   "source": [
    "# Understanding Grover's Algorithm: A Step-by-Step Jupyter Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** [Your Name]\n",
    "**Course:** Quantum Computing Capstone\n",
    "**Date:** 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook guides you through Grover's algorithm interactively.\n",
    "Each cell builds on the previous one, so run them in order."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1: Setup and Imports\n",
    "\n",
    "First, let's import the necessary libraries and verify our installation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Core quantum computing libraries\n",
    "from qiskit import QuantumCircuit\n",
    "from qiskit.quantum_info import Statevector\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import plot_histogram, plot_bloch_multivector\n",
    "\n",
    "# Numerical and plotting\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Our custom modules\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('..')\n",
    "from src.grover import two_qubit_grover_11, four_qubit_grover\n",
    "from src.simulation import simulate_statevector, print_probabilities\n",
    "from src.gates import print_circuit_info\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Setup complete! All libraries imported successfully.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2: The Qubit and Superposition\n",
    "\n",
    "Before Grover's algorithm, let's understand the building blocks.\n",
    "\n",
    "A qubit can be in state `|0>`, `|1>`, or a superposition of both.\n",
    "The Hadamard gate creates superposition."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a single qubit in superposition\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Circuit:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# See the statevector\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print(f"\nStatevector: {state.data}")\n",
    "print(f"Probability of |0>: {abs(state.data[0])**2:.4f}")\n",
    "print(f"Probability of |1>: {abs(state.data[1])**2:.4f}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: Two-Qubit Superposition\n",
    "\n",
    "With 2 qubits, we can create superposition over 4 states simultaneously.\n",
    "This is the starting point for Grover's algorithm."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create uniform superposition over 2 qubits\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h([0, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Circuit:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print("\nStatevector breakdown:")\n",
    "for i, amp in enumerate(state.data):\n",
    "    bits = format(i, '02b')\n",
    "    prob = abs(amp)**2\n",
    "    print(f"|{bits}>: amplitude={amp:.4f}, probability={prob:.4f}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 4: The Oracle — Tagging the Solution\n",
    "\n",
    "The oracle applies a phase flip to the solution state.\n",
    "For 2 qubits and solution `|11>`, the CZ gate does this automatically."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build circuit: superposition + oracle\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h([0, 1])\n",
    "qc.cz(0, 1)  # Oracle: tags |11>\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Circuit after oracle:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print("\nState after oracle:")\n",
    "for i, amp in enumerate(state.data):\n",
    "    bits = format(i, '02b')\n",
    "    print(f"|{bits}>: amplitude={amp:.4f}")\n",
    "\n",
    "print("\nNotice: |11> now has a NEGATIVE amplitude!")\n",
    "print("But probabilities haven't changed yet (all still 25%).")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 5: The Diffusion Operator — Amplification\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we apply the diffusion operator to amplify the tagged solution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Complete 2-qubit Grover circuit\n",
    "qc = two_qubit_grover_11()\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Complete Grover circuit:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "probs = simulate_statevector(qc)\n",
    "print_probabilities(probs, solution="11")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 6: Four-Qubit Grover's Algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "Now let's see the full 4-qubit version with multiple iterations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Choose a solution to search for\n",
    "solution = "0010"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build the circuit\n",
    "qc = four_qubit_grover(solution)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Circuit for solution |{solution}>:")\n",
    "print_circuit_info(qc)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate\n",
    "probs = simulate_statevector(qc)\n",
    "print_probabilities(probs, solution=solution)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 7: Visualizing with Matplotlib\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's create a nice bar chart of the probabilities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create bar chart\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "states = list(probs.keys())\n",
    "probabilities = [probs[s] for s in states]\n",
    "colors = ['red' if s == solution else 'blue' for s in states]\n",
    "\n",
    "bars = ax.bar(states, probabilities, color=colors)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Quantum State')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Probability')\n",
    "ax.set_title(f"Grover\\'s Algorithm: Solution |{solution}>")\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add value labels on bars\n",
    "for bar, prob in zip(bars, probabilities):\n",
    "    height = bar.get_height()\n",
    "    if height > 0.01:\n",
    "        ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,\n",
    "                f'{prob:.3f}',\n",
    "                ha='center', va='bottom')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 8: Experimenting with Different Solutions\n",
    "\n",
    "Try changing the solution string and re-running the cells above!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Try different solutions\n",
    "test_solutions = ["0000", "1111", "1010", "0101"]\n",
    "\n",
    "for sol in test_solutions:\n",
    "    qc = four_qubit_grover(sol)\n",
    "    probs = simulate_statevector(qc)\n",
    "    max_state = max(probs, key=probs.get)\n",
    "    max_prob = probs[max_state]\n",
    "    print(f"|{sol}>: found |{max_state}> with {max_prob*100:.1f}% probability")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "You've now seen Grover's algorithm in action!\n",
    "\n",
    "Key takeaways:\n",
    "1. **Superposition** lets us check all states simultaneously\n",
    "2. **Oracle** tags the solution with a phase flip\n",
    "3. **Diffusion** amplifies the tagged solution through interference\n",
    "4. **Quadratic speedup**: sqrt(N) instead of N queries\n",
    "\n",
    "Next steps:\n",
    "- Try running on real quantum hardware via IBM Quantum\n",
    "- Generalize to more qubits\n",
    "- Explore other quantum algorithms (Shor, VQE, QAOA)"
   ]
  }
